Notes: Current and historical U.S. Geological Survey topographic maps; late 19th and early 20th-century Sanborn Fire Insurance maps of the State of Georgia; topographic map sets for most countries in various scales; worldwide nautical and aeronautical charts; select thematic, country and city maps from around the world with an emphasis on the United States and the State of Georgia; general reference, national, historical and thematic atlases; aerial photography, primarily of the State of Georgia; journals related to map collections and map librarianship; gazetteers and place name guides; cartographic reference materials.
